   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## Load processed datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "In this step, we load the training and test datasets generated by the data ingestion notebook.These datasets are stored as serialized pickle files to ensure reproducibility and a clear separation between data ingestion and preprocessing.No transformations are applied at this stage.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "92d08b26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(574945, 341) (107, 336)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Imports + paths\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import scipy\n",
    "\n",
    "DATA_PROCESSED = Path(\"../data/processed\")\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(DATA_PROCESSED / \"train.pkl\", \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "    train_df = pickle.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(DATA_PROCESSED / \"test.pkl\", \"rb\") as f:\n",
    "    test_df = pickle.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(train_df.shape, test_df.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "308c7380",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## Identify identifier and label columns\n",
    "\n",
    "This step defines columns that should not be used as model features.Identifier columns describe rows, sequences, or subjects, while label columns represent target variables.These columns are excluded to prevent data leakage and ensure that only sensor-driven measurements are used as inputs.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "72fd13eb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Train feature cols: 334\n",
      "Test feature cols : 332\n",
      "Common feature cols: 332\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ID_COLS = [\"sequence_id\",\"row_id\",\"sequence_counter\", \"subject\", \"phase\"]\n",
    "LABEL_COLS = [\"gesture\", \"behavior\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "NON_FEATURE_COLS = set(ID_COLS + LABEL_COLS)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select feature columns\n",
    "train_feature_cols = [c for c in train_df.columns if c not in NON_FEATURE_COLS]\n",
    "test_feature_cols  = [c for c in test_df.columns  if c not in NON_FEATURE_COLS]\n",
    "\n",
    "feature_cols = sorted(list(set(train_feature_cols).intersection(test_feature_cols)))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Train feature cols:\", len(train_feature_cols))\n",
    "print(\"Test feature cols :\", len(test_feature_cols))\n",
    "print(\"Common feature cols:\", len(feature_cols))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5282d60c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Clean invalid sensor values\n",
    "Invalid sensor readings are indicated by a value of -1.0 in the dataset.These values are replaced with NaN to explicitly represent missing measurements, allowing them to be handled appropriately during imputation and normalization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "fccdf109",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Make a copy of original Dataframe\n",
    "def clean_invalid_values(df, feature_cols):\n",
    "    df = df.copy()\n",
    "    df[feature_cols] = df[feature_cols].replace(-1.0, np.nan)\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "#Return clean Dataframe\n",
    "train_df = clean_invalid_values(train_df, feature_cols)\n",
    "test_df  = clean_invalid_values(test_df, feature_cols)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f7a806b8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Filter short sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "Sequences with fewer than a minimum number of timesteps are removed from the training dataset. This ensures that all retained sequences provide sufficient temporal context for sequence-based models such as CNNs, LSTMs, and BiLSTMs. The test dataset is left unchanged.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "f7d48d1a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "MIN_LEN = 35\n",
    "\n",
    "seq_len = train_df.groupby(\"sequence_id\").size()\n",
    "keep_ids = seq_len[seq_len >= MIN_LEN].index\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df = train_df[train_df[\"sequence_id\"].isin(keep_ids)].copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "21e74335",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Impute missing values using training statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing sensor values (NaNs) are imputed using the median of each feature, computed from the training data only.The same imputation values are applied to the test data to maintain consistency and prevent data leakage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "caf00cdf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fill_values = train_df[feature_cols].median(numeric_only=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df[feature_cols] = train_df[feature_cols].fillna(fill_values)\n",
    "test_df[feature_cols]  = test_df[feature_cols].fillna(fill_values)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e50d8c04",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Normalize sensor features\n",
    "\n",
    "Sensor features are standardized using z-score normalization.Feature-wise mean and standard deviation are computed from the training data only and applied to both training and test datasets to avoid data leakage and improve model stability.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "b9ee7443",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mu = train_df[feature_cols].mean(numeric_only=True)\n",
    "sigma = train_df[feature_cols].std(numeric_only=True).replace(0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df[feature_cols] = (train_df[feature_cols] - mu) / sigma\n",
    "test_df[feature_cols]  = (test_df[feature_cols]  - mu) / sigma"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "049a04dc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "NaNs train: 0\n",
      "NaNs test : 0\n",
      "Train sequences: 8146\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"NaNs train:\", train_df[feature_cols].isna().sum().sum())\n",
    "print(\"NaNs test :\", test_df[feature_cols].isna().sum().sum())\n",
    "print(\"Train sequences:\", train_df[\"sequence_id\"].nunique())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1a90af8a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "## Save cleaned datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "After preprocessing, the cleaned and normalized training and test datasets are serialized and saved as separate artifacts.These files serve as standardized inputs for downstream sequence construction and model training notebooks, ensuring reproducibility and modularity of the pipeline.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "f3646466",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Saved cleaned datasets\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with open(DATA_PROCESSED / \"train_clean.pkl\", \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "    pickle.dump(train_df, f)\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(DATA_PROCESSED / \"test_clean.pkl\", \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "    pickle.dump(test_df, f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Saved cleaned datasets\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "af0d1cd6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Feature Engineering for Specific Models (FFT & Reshaping)\n",
    "\n",
    "To reproduce the models described in the research paper, we need two specific data transformations:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.  FFT Features (Frequency Domain): The MLP model takes frequency-domain features as input. We will apply a Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) to the IMU and Thermopile sensors.\n",
    "2.  TOF Reshaping (Spatial Domain): The CNN-BiLSTM model treats the Time-of-Flight (TOF) sensor data as an $8 \\times 8$ image grid. We need to identify these columns and prepare a function to reshape them during training.\n"
   ]
  },
